Every Mg-ATP dependent process and enzyme in the body is magnesium dependent.  3,751 protein types in the human body have mangesium specific receptors to optimize their functionality. snippet.textDisplay: @Sherry StacyRN UVB radiation is required to produce vitamin D3 in the skin. This can be found in sunbeds. However, repeated exposure to UVB radiation can also cause DNA damage in skin epithelial cells which can increase the risk of melanoma and non‐melanoma skin cancer. I think the data is pretty clear on this. Several meta‐analyses have consistently shown that sunbed use increases melanoma risk by 15–25%. For this reason, I personally choose to supplement with vitamin D3. The ability to synthesize vitamin D with a given amount of UV exposure is also highly subject to individual variation even outside of the seasonality aspect.

I will add that I am unvaccinated and the doctor and nurses just expected me to die.  They told me this after I survived.  How did I survive?  They found that I was Vitamin D deficient.  Once they started me on the once a week 50000 Vitamin D pill, my lungs started to clear up and I started to feel so much better.  I tested COVID negative and was able to go home.  I completed avoided the ICU.  They want me to take the Vitamin D for the rest of my life because I have also shown to be deficient in the past.
